1
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:09,640
Boss.

2
00:01:09,920 --> 00:01:11,650
Two steamed buns to go, please.

3
00:01:17,039 --> 00:01:17,520
I got it.

4
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:20,840
Keep it.

5
00:01:22,039 --> 00:01:22,520
Thanks.

6
00:01:24,039 --> 00:01:24,840
Thanks, boss.

7
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:26,210
Let's go.

8
00:01:45,880 --> 00:01:48,320
Ye Qiming was indeed at the construction site today.

9
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:50,180
We're here to see Ye Qiming's car.

10
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:53,380
We'll see what we can find.

11
00:01:58,160 --> 00:01:58,840
Bro.

12
00:01:58,960 --> 00:01:59,800
Can I ask you something?

13
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:02,560
Um, are you an employee of Tongda?

14
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:04,480
We're just migrant workers.

15
00:02:04,480 --> 00:02:05,920
We go wherever there's work.

16
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:07,640
So we're not really employees.

17
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:09,720
How is it working for Tongda?

18
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,100
It's nothing special.

19
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:15,360
They just build things up and tear them down.

20
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:15,880
I heard

21
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:18,079
the higher-ups can't agree on things.

22
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:19,280
As long as they pay us, it's fine.

23
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:19,920
Who cares.

24
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:20,920
What nonsense are you talking about?

25
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:21,960
This is the manager, right?

26
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:22,480
Manager.

27
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,160
Thanks, bro.

28
00:02:23,160 --> 00:02:23,920
Hello, manager.

29
00:02:23,920 --> 00:02:24,640
Sorry.

30
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,040
Manager.

31
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:28,560
You two.

32
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:30,520
What are you doing? What's the matter?

33
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:32,520
We want to ask about jobs.

34
00:02:34,440 --> 00:02:35,770
What do you want to know?

35
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,120
Does this site

36
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:38,760
operate 24 hours a day?

37
00:02:41,640 --> 00:02:43,320
We are different from other companies.

38
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:45,160
Other companies don't let their employees rest.

39
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:47,090
Tongda operates on a shift system.

40
00:02:48,040 --> 00:02:49,760
So that means sometimes

41
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,700
there's no one watching the site?

42
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,079
No one watching?

43
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,680
There are people watching even when there's no construction.

44
00:02:58,680 --> 00:02:59,480
Don't get any funny ideas.

45
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,040
No.

46
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,600
We just wanted to see if you're hiring.

47
00:03:01,600 --> 00:03:01,960
Yes.

48
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:03,080
Just getting some info.

49
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:04,040
We won't bother you anymore.

50
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:05,240
Thanks, manager.

51
00:03:05,440 --> 00:03:05,960
Thank you.

52
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,960
Thanks, manager.

53
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:16,240
Master, we found Qian Yong's whereabouts.

54
00:03:19,920 --> 00:03:20,480
Na,

55
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:23,079
the policeman you know.

56
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:25,160
They actually came to the construction site today.

57
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:27,090
You mean they have their eyes on us?

58
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,560
Doesn't look like it.

59
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,079
It should just be

60
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,370
a routine visit.

61
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:35,680
Okay.

62
00:03:35,960 --> 00:03:37,890
Keep me posted if there's any news.

63
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,280
It's been so long, Sister Na.

64
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:41,720
Don't you trust me?

65
00:03:56,680 --> 00:03:58,240
What's wrong with you?

66
00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:00,520
Why are you staying outside?

67
00:04:00,720 --> 00:04:02,120
I had a fight with Qiming.

68
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,090
I don't want to stay at home.

69
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:05,500
What happened?

70
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,560
Did he bully you?

71
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,290
Don't worry.

72
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,360
I will go settle the score with him.

73
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,220
It's fine, Dad.

74
00:04:11,480 --> 00:04:12,480
I'm all grown up.

75
00:04:13,280 --> 00:04:15,000
I can handle my own problems.

76
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:16,930
You guys should go back.

77
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,360
I can't just let this go.

78
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:30,840
Hello?

79
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,600
Is this Ye Qiming?

80
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:35,560
Get your ass to the hospital right now,

81
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,560
as fast as you can.

82
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:42,120
Why the rush? What's the matter?

83
00:04:43,040 --> 00:04:43,640
Come here.

84
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,120
Let me ask you.

85
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:48,970
I entrusted my daughter to you.

86
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,780
How did you take care of her

87
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:52,880
to let her end up in the hospital?

88
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:55,040
What happened to Xia Lin?

89
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,370
You let her go out alone,

90
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,000
and she got into a car accident.

91
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:58,860
A car accident?

92
00:04:58,960 --> 00:04:59,560
Is it serious?

93
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,680
Okay, okay.

94
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,720
Don't shed crocodile tears.

95
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,400
If you can take care of her, do it.

96
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:06,560
If not, leave her to us.

97
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,800
We'll take care of her.

98
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,440
Just stay away from her, okay?

99
00:05:09,440 --> 00:05:09,840
Dad,

100
00:05:10,160 --> 00:05:11,690
you can't say that about me.

101
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:12,640
Right now, it's Xia Lin.

102
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,400
She is bossing me around and blaming me.

103
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:15,530
I'm the victim here.

104
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:16,320
What?

105
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:18,320
You feel wronged?

106
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,380
I really regret it.

107
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,800
I shouldn't have let my daughter

108
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,130
marry someone like you.

109
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:26,080
If anything happens to her in the future,

110
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:26,940
remember this.

111
00:05:27,400 --> 00:05:28,460
I won't let you off.

112
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:48,760
Your loan is overdue.

113
00:05:49,080 --> 00:05:50,680
This is our second reminder.

114
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:53,520
If you don't pay up, you'll face the consequences.

115
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:56,200
People getting their hands chopped off for not paying,

116
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:58,000
you've heard about that, right?

117
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,159
Loan.

118
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:00,960
Installment.

119
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,130
Call me from your phone.

120
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:14,560
Damn.

121
00:06:16,400 --> 00:06:17,060
11 o'clock.

122
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:17,730
Harvest.

123
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:32,040
You're still in the mood to look at the menu.

124
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:33,760
It's past 11 and he's not here yet.

125
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,220
Do you think he spotted us?

126
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:35,880
No.

127
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:37,570
They are testing us.

128
00:06:40,960 --> 00:06:41,560
When we came,

129
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,280
do you think someone followed us?

130
00:06:43,280 --> 00:06:44,080
You don't look like a student at all.

131
00:06:44,080 --> 00:06:44,840
Did they spot us?

132
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:46,360
No, I checked.

133
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,380
Captain Jiang.

134
00:06:54,840 --> 00:06:55,200
Come.

135
00:06:55,560 --> 00:06:56,480
Please come in.

136
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:58,290
We've been waiting for a while.

137
00:06:58,720 --> 00:06:59,320
Police.

138
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,560
Come, take a seat.

139
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,760
Come, let's order some food.

140
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:03,290
Come sit.

141
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,600
I... I didn't do anything wrong.

142
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:10,040
Why did you run if you did nothing wrong?

143
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,560
I will ask you a few questions.

144
00:07:11,560 --> 00:07:12,960
Answer them truthfully.

145
00:07:13,960 --> 00:07:15,560
What kind of company is this?

146
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:18,080
Tengfei Credit Company.

147
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,220
Is it legal?

148
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:20,200
Of course.

149
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:21,880
We are a legitimate company.

150
00:07:21,880 --> 00:07:22,880
You can look it up.

151
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:25,410
What's your main business?

152
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:26,520
Credit loans.

153
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:28,120
What's the loan process?

154
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:29,920
You just need to provide your ID,

155
00:07:30,640 --> 00:07:31,360
phone number,

156
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,120
student ID, class, major,

157
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:34,640
home address,

158
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:37,600
and parents' names.

159
00:07:38,520 --> 00:07:41,159
Then record an online signing video.

160
00:07:42,240 --> 00:07:43,280
The most important part is

161
00:07:43,280 --> 00:07:45,320
writing the loan amount clearly,

162
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:46,880
and then you're done.

163
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,880
How much did Lu Yang borrow from you?

164
00:07:49,840 --> 00:07:50,300
30,000.

165
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,320
What about the interest?

166
00:07:52,320 --> 00:07:53,159
The interest isn't high,

167
00:07:53,159 --> 00:07:54,200
24 percent.

168
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:55,960
24 percent isn't high?

169
00:07:58,360 --> 00:08:00,520
So how many people borrowed money from you,

170
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:01,040
or rather,

171
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:02,770
how many schools are involved?

172
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,760
About a hundred people.

173
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:06,600
Roughly,

174
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:09,280
from dozens of schools.

175
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:12,040
So you used threats and intimidation

176
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,360
to force Lu Yang to pay the money back,

177
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:14,960
leading to his death, right?

178
00:08:15,200 --> 00:08:15,880
He died?

179
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,480
Then what about his money?

180
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,810
Forget about the money.

181
00:08:19,760 --> 00:08:22,090
Explain clearly what happened to Lu Yang.

182
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:25,280
Speak.

183
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,330
OK, we'll tell you everything.

184
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,440
That day, I watched Lu Yang.

185
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:32,720
I noticed his eyes

186
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:36,400
kept looking at my colleague.

187
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:40,080
I could tell from his eyes

188
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:43,520
that he might just be interested in this woman.

189
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,890
What brings you here today?

190
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,680
Which drink would you like?

191
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:49,080
The most expensive one.

192
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:50,000
Okay.

193
00:08:50,640 --> 00:08:52,300
Get the most expensive drink.

194
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:00,940
Do you see that guy over there?

195
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:10,880
Handsome.

196
00:09:11,280 --> 00:09:12,160
Are you alone?

197
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:14,040
Yes.

198
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,280
Let's have a drink.

199
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:30,320
Long time no see.

200
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:32,160
How have you been lately?

201
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:33,820
Come often when you have time.

202
00:09:35,680 --> 00:09:37,560
I felt like the opportunity had come.

203
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:38,920
So I...

204
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,680
contacted that girl from the bar.

205
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,000
Wait a minute.

206
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:46,250
Is the girl from this bar named Xiaoju?

207
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:52,400
How many times did Lu Yang borrow money from you?

208
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:52,800
He...

209
00:09:53,160 --> 00:09:54,240
He only took out a loan once.

210
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,840
But he could never pay it off.

211
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,120
He'd pay a little back each time,

212
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,480
but always in cash.

213
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:01,280
Did he have any other sources of income?

214
00:10:01,600 --> 00:10:03,560
I... I don't know about that.

215
00:10:04,240 --> 00:10:06,440
But he owed us so much money,

216
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,210
yet he went drinking every day.

217
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,760
Think about it. Dating a bar girl

218
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,120
must cost a fortune.

219
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:15,160
His little income definitely wasn't enough.

220
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:15,820
Is that all?

221
00:10:16,880 --> 00:10:18,880
I've... I've said everything I know.

222
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:19,410
Let's go.

223
00:10:19,640 --> 00:10:21,880
Come back to the station with us for investigation.

224
00:10:21,880 --> 00:10:23,600
Can we get leniency?

225
00:10:24,080 --> 00:10:25,600
That depends on your attitude in pleading guilty.

226
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:27,260
Let's go. Back to the station.

227
00:10:29,320 --> 00:10:29,960
Get up.

228
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,120
Move.

229
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,660
Liu Xiaoju.

230
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:34,880
We meet again.

231
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:39,210
I didn't really want to meet like this.

232
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:41,280
You hid a lot from us last time.

233
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:42,400
Tell the truth today.

234
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,480
It will be good for you.

235
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,960
I didn't hide anything last time.

236
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:45,320
Well,

237
00:10:45,480 --> 00:10:47,520
didn't I answer everything you asked?

238
00:10:47,520 --> 00:10:48,380
You didn't ask,

239
00:10:48,920 --> 00:10:50,050
so how is it my fault?

240
00:10:50,280 --> 00:10:53,280
How much money did Tengfei Company actually give you?

241
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,120
One thousand.

242
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:57,360
One thousand.

243
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:58,800
Just for a thousand bucks,

244
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,200
you dragged Lu Yang into this?

245
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,730
Do you know this is illegal?

246
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:03,800
I didn't know.

247
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:04,880
They just told me

248
00:11:04,880 --> 00:11:07,080
to bring a customer from the bar to the hotel.

249
00:11:07,080 --> 00:11:09,440
And they'd give me a thousand bucks as commission.

250
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,480
I didn't agree at first.

251
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:12,360
Later, when I went back,

252
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:14,020
I talked it over with my girls.

253
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:16,500
They said since it has a business license

254
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,200
and a contract,

255
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,360
it must be legal.

256
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,970
How could it be illegal now?

257
00:11:20,400 --> 00:11:22,880
I was short on cash at the time, so I agreed.

258
00:11:22,920 --> 00:11:24,480
This... it can't be illegal.

259
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,080
You must have made a mistake.

260
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:28,400
Lu Yang took out a lot of campus loans.

261
00:11:28,400 --> 00:11:30,160
Did he have any other money besides that?

262
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,440
I don't know. I really don't know.

263
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:34,360
You are suspected of extortion.

264
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:36,240
You will be criminally detained according to the law.

265
00:11:36,240 --> 00:11:36,600
Li.

266
00:11:37,040 --> 00:11:37,720
Captain Shen.

267
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:38,560
Contact our colleagues

268
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:39,360
and take them down.

269
00:11:39,360 --> 00:11:39,800
On it.

270
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,970
You... you can't arrest me.

271
00:11:42,040 --> 00:11:43,000
I don't know anything.

272
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,200
Why are you arresting me?

273
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:46,040
I... what I did was legal.

274
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,280
It's not illegal. You...

275
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:48,410
Check again. Get up.

276
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:49,640
You can't arrest me.

277
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,440
We'll tear down the partition walls

278
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,440
and rebuild them.

279
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,080
Mr. Yu means

280
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,840
the first floor stays as it is,

281
00:11:56,840 --> 00:11:59,480
and the floors above will follow the latest blueprints.

282
00:11:59,480 --> 00:11:59,920
No.

283
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,360
Tear it down immediately.

284
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,420
The company would suffer a huge loss.

285
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:05,480
The loss has nothing to do with you.

286
00:12:05,480 --> 00:12:07,520
If there's a technical issue, you'll be responsible.

287
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:08,120
I...

288
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,840
I can't take that responsibility.

289
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,360
If you can't, do as I say.

290
00:12:17,840 --> 00:12:18,320
Yu Na.

291
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,280
I told you,

292
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,240
you must listen to me on engineering matters.

293
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:24,040
I need the support of the people.

294
00:12:26,440 --> 00:12:27,520
What's wrong with you?

295
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:28,650
Why are you so angry?

296
00:12:28,720 --> 00:12:29,960
I told you to tear it down and rebuild it.

297
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:31,490
Tear it down and rebuild it!

298
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,720
Don't you understand?

299
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,480
No, we'll renovate the first floor.

300
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:36,400
We gave the buyers a 10% discount.

301
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,600
They won't complain.

302
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:40,240
But we can't just lose over a million for nothing.

303
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,920
You only see what's in front of you.

304
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,160
Do you know what time it is?

305
00:12:43,160 --> 00:12:44,560
It's the bidding period.

306
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:46,040
Once we lose our credibility,

307
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,800
it means losing the western suburbs project's

308
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:49,200
bidding qualification.

309
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:53,880
Don't be so fierce.

310
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:54,920
I was wrong.

311
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:57,440
Tell me,

312
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:58,960
do you just not want me

313
00:12:58,960 --> 00:13:00,090
to get this project?

314
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:02,690
What are you talking about? I love you so much.

315
00:13:06,200 --> 00:13:07,600
No matter what you think,

316
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,160
whatever the cost,

317
00:13:09,880 --> 00:13:11,880
I must get this project.

318
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:25,220
Then you have to win me over first.

319
00:13:28,640 --> 00:13:30,720
According to interviews with nearby residents,

320
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:32,160
this man is named Qian Yong.

321
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:34,620
He moved to the urban village just a week ago.

322
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,240
Since it was a short-term lease,

323
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,040
he only gave Mr. Deng a few hundred yuan,

324
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:39,360
and they didn't sign a contract.

325
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:39,880
Li,

326
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,160
can you track down this Qian Yong directly?

327
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:43,120
I can't, sir.

328
00:13:43,280 --> 00:13:45,000
I can't find him in the system at all.

329
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,800
What his real name is doesn't matter.

330
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,260
It doesn't matter if his name is real or fake.

331
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,080
Zhao,

332
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,480
The important thing is to find this guy.

333
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,760
I had a colleague look into it.

334
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:54,420
This person

335
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,760
moved to the urban village after Tian Liang died.

336
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:59,220
We finally found Lu Yang through Tian Liang,

337
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:00,440
and then Lu Yang died.

338
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:01,480
You mean

339
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:02,860
he moved in a week early

340
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:04,200
just to observe Lu Yang?

341
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,130
I'm not sure yet.

342
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,840
I asked Team Two to look into it.

343
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:08,320
Right now, we only have three priorities.

344
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:08,720
First,

345
00:14:09,000 --> 00:14:10,360
continue investigating both cases'

346
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,720
only common contact,

347
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:12,380
Xia Lin.

348
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:13,340
Second,

349
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,280
continue investigating everyone around Lu Yang.

350
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:15,880
Third.

351
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:17,360
I don't care what his name is,

352
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:18,560
or who he is.

353
00:14:18,880 --> 00:14:20,120
Issue a wanted poster.

354
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,080
Don't let him get away.
